# Three DataFrame types — keep them straight

## All called "DataFrame" — very different

- **pandas** (`pandas.DataFrame`) — **driver memory only**
  - Final-mile analysis, plotting, small fixtures
- **Pandas-on-Spark** (`pyspark.pandas.DataFrame`) — **distributed**
  - pandas *syntax* at Spark *scale*
- **Spark** (`pyspark.sql.DataFrame`) — **distributed**
  - Native API — best performance, most features

## The key relationship

- The first is single-machine; the other two are distributed on the same engine
- Pandas-on-Spark = a Spark DataFrame **+ a pandas-style index** (→ next two gotchas)
